Source: Australian Broadcast Co., Tue 31 Oct 2000 [edited
<http://www.abc.net.au/ra/newsdaily/s206470.htm>

Rift River fever sweeping through Saudi Arabia and Yemen
--------------------------------------------------------
The death toll from Rift Valley Fever is growing in both Yemen and Saudi
Arabia since it first appeared in early September.
Yemen's Health And Agriculture Ministries say 109 people have died and 2742
head of livestock have been put down since the disease appeared.
The Saudi Health Ministry says 91 people in the kingdom have died out of a
total of 508 cases, while 325 patients had recovered and left hospital.
